snippet.textDisplay: Kalasha were the first people who  ruled most of the area now lower chitral as the kho ( the indigenous people of  chitral state ruled the upper part of the state like mastuj mulkhow torkhaw on some occasions in yasin  in Gilgit baltistan as its border share a significant  area with it . The kalasha speak kasha war means the language if the kalasha peoples while the kho or chetrari  refers chitrali in down district bez of the language we speak has many heavy notes and some vowels and words which dont exist in urdu or pushta nor english . A lyrics in the songs goes : ta hata 'a sozem e sohorum khursi ay "  in khowar language  it goes : tate sawzem e sohorum khursi ae " with such little difference it is dicate the culture integration that took place centuries ago still has some remnants remained in it   After their defeat the were restricted to the three valleys known as kalash valleys Rumboor bumburate and birirsome main settlements are still known as the ancestral names given by the kalsaha such as the chew bridge at chitral town . The kalasha settlements were seen   in the outskirts of sueer and ayun in  the last couple of centuries  of the millennium but now their total population is about2700. Left

The kalasha speak kasha war means the language if the kalasha peoples while the kho or chetrari  refers chitrali in down district bez of the language we speak has many heavy notes and some vowels and words which dont exist in urdu or pushta nor english . A lyrics in the songs goes : ta hata 'a sozem e sohorum khursi ay "  in khowar language  it goes : tate sawzem e sohorum khursi ae " with such little difference it is dicate the culture integration that took place centuries ago still has some remnants remained in it   After their defeat the were restricted to the three valleys known as kalash valleys Rumboor bumburate and birirsome main settlements are still known as the ancestral names given by the kalsaha such as the chew bridge at chitral town . snippet.textDisplay: Kalash people are the real ones who didn't forget their culture.. still perform the Vedic way of life and Hinduism as their religion, much respect to their dedication. They're the real descendants of early Indo-Aryan community that settled in Indus Valley. Though I listen to Coke Studio now and then but didn't know that any such folk song of Kalash people exist on this platform until my History teacher talked about the same. Thanks Coke Studio for bringing such hidden culture to the mainstream. Kudos to your efforts :)
